cancer<-data[grep(pattern="Cancer",data[,1]),]
cancer<-rbind(data[1,],cancer)
normal<-data[grep(pattern="Normal",data[,1]),]
normal<-rbind(data[1,],normal)
#cancer[1:3,]
#normal[1:3,]

normal<-t(normal)
imputeNO<-lapply(2:(dim(normal)[1]),function(x){
    half_LOD=0.5*as.numeric(as.character(normal[x,1]))
    #half_LOD
    feature<-normal[x,]
    feature[is.na(feature)]<-half_LOD
    #feature
    return(feature)
      } )

cancer<-t(cancer)
imputeCAN<-lapply(2:(dim(cancer)[1]),function(x){

    #half_LOD

    feature[is.na(feature)]<-half_LOD
    #feature
    return(feature)
      } )

normal<-as.data.frame(do.call(rbind,imputeNO),stringsAsFactors = F)

cal<-lapply(1:(dim(dataImpute)[1]),function(x){
    name<-row.names(dataImpute[x,])
    sd<-sd(dataImpute[x,])
    max<-max(dataImpute[x,])
    min<-min(dataImpute[x,])
    mean<-sum(dataImpute[x,])/dim(dataImpute)[2]
    re<-c(name,mean,sd,max,min)
    return(re)
  } )

lm(Group~.,data=data_age_merge)

library(glmnet)
data_age_merge=na.omit(data_age_merge)
x=model.matrix(Group~.,data_age_merge)[,-1]
y=data_age_merge$Group

#set training set vs testing set 7:3
index = sample(1:nrow(data_age_merge), 0.7*nrow(data_age_merge)) 
train = data_age_merge[index,] # Create the training data 
test = data_age_merge[-index,] # Create the test data
x = as.matrix(train[,-1])
y_train = train$Group
x_test = as.matrix(test[,-1])
y_test = test$Group

# Setting alpha = 1 implements lasso regression，use default lambdas
#lambdas <- 10^seq(2, -3, by = -.1)
#lasso_reg <- cv.glmnet(x, y_train,alpha = 1, lambda = lambdas, standardize = F)

#train the lasso model
lasso_model <- cv.glmnet(x, y_train,alpha = 1, standardize = F)
#plot(lasso_reg)

set.seed(552) 
cv.out=cv.glmnet(x,y_train,family = "binomial",alpha=1)#交叉验证
plot(cv.out)
bestlam1=cv.out$lambda.min
bestlam2=cv.out$lambda.1se
#see result for each feature. select not 0 valuse, 绝对值越大影响越大
#coef(lasso_model)

#select best lambda，基于交叉验证得到的最好lambda，更新迷行
lambda_best=min(bestlam1,bestlam2)
#lambda_best

# Compute R^2 from true and predicted values
eval_results <- function(true, predicted, df) {
  SSE <- sum((predicted - true)^2)
  SST <- sum((true - mean(true))^2)
  R_square <- 1 - SSE / SST
  RMSE = sqrt(SSE/nrow(df))
  # Model performance metrics
  data.frame(RMSE = RMSE,Rsquare = R_square)
}

#generate the predictions and print the evaluation metrics for both the training and test datasets
predictions_train <- predict(lasso_model, s = lambda_best, newx = x)
predict(lasso_model, s = lambda_best, newx = x)
predict(lasso_model,s=c(bestlam1,bestlam2),newx=x,type="coefficients") 
eval_results(y_train, predictions_train, train)

predictions_test <- predict(lasso_model, s = lambda_best, newx = x_test)
eval_results(y_test, predictions_test, test)
